\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}
Let $\Omega\subset M$ be a bounded region of the Trawinistic manifold.  
Boundary conditions on $\partial\Omega$ force the Trawinistic Laplacian to admit eigenmodes:

\begin{equation}
-\Delta_T \phi_n = \lambda_n\phi_n .
\end{equation}

For a massive field, the frequency of each mode satisfies the dispersion relation:

\begin{equation}
\omega_n^2=\lambda_n+m^2 .
\end{equation}

Thus confinement converts continuous spectral freedom into a discrete mode family.

\paragraph{Interpretation.}
Geometry and boundary conditions discretize allowed field frequencies.
